review_blob: Smelled like fermented fruit. Tasted a bit floral. I liked it better at our near room temp.
Very refreshing. Perfect for these hot Florida evenings. Slight citrus taste but nicely muted.
Bread and salt.  Not really a strong flavor and wimps out in the end. nice warming sensation however. Not a keeper for me.
Excellent ale. Glad to see more restaurants carry this awesome beer. A dark amber beer with a pine bitter flavor and a bold after taste.
